Asymetrix renamed itself to click2learn.com in Oct 1999. In 2003, that entity was effectively merged with Docent into SumTotal Systems (www.sumtotalsystems.com), a subsidiary of SkillSoft (www.skillsoft.com). SumTotal still supports ToolBook at tb.sumtotalsystems.com.

Transquest began as a joint venture between Delta Airlines and AT&T in 1995, then became a wholly owned subsidiary of Delta Airlines in July 1996, before being renamed to Delta Technology in 1997, and finally being repurchased by Delta Airlines in 2009.
NOVA Information Systems (NOVA), a wholly-owned subsidiary of U.S. Bancorp (NYSE: USB) became Elavon in April 2008.
